<subSubSection id="BADD651FFFDAFFEA29F68FC0FE51F79E" pageId="4" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="F2783694FFDAFFEA29F68FC0FE51F79E" blockId="4.[136,1452,1567,2062]" pageId="4">
<emphasis id="C0B3EA86FFDAFFEA29F68FC0FED2F958" bold="true" box="[189,328,1710,1736]" pageId="4">Comments:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName id="35C74D17FFDAFFEA282F8FC1FDF8F959" authorityName="Zambrano &amp; Solano. A. Habit. B. Flower" authorityYear="2021" box="[356,610,1711,1737]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Epidendrum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="4" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="amoanum">
<emphasis id="C0B3EA86FFDAFFEA282F8FC1FDF8F959" box="[356,610,1711,1737]" italics="true" pageId="4">Epidendrum amoanum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs to the Diothonea group, and is recognized by the oblong-lanceolate leaves, amber-yellow flowers, elliptic dorsal sepal, oblong, erose petals, and a sub-3-lobed lip with seven minute keels and truncate apex. The most similar species is the Peruvian 
<emphasis id="C0B3EA86FFDAFFEA2A7B8F96FC48F881" box="[816,978,1784,1809]" italics="true" pageId="4">
<taxonomicName id="35C74D17FFDAFFEA2A7B8F96FC54F881" authorityName="Hagsater, Collantes &amp; Santiago" authorityYear="2006" box="[816,974,1784,1809]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Epidendrum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="4" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="amaruense">E. amaruënse</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
but it differs in the smaller plants (
<quantity id="353F9B71FFDAFFEA2C2F8F99FA31F881" box="[1380,1451,1783,1809]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="4" unit="cm" value="20.0">20 cm</quantity>
<emphasis id="C0B3EA86FFDAFFEA29C38E72FF3DF8A5" box="[136,167,1820,1845]" italics="true" pageId="4">vs.</emphasis>
<quantity id="353F9B71FFDAFFEA29FB8E75FF62F8A5" box="[176,248,1819,1845]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="4" unit="cm" value="40.0">40 cm</quantity>
tall), linear-lanceolate leaves (
<emphasis id="C0B3EA86FFDAFFEA2B158E72FDE6F8A5" box="[606,636,1820,1845]" italics="true" pageId="4">vs.</emphasis>
oblong-lanceolate), non-resupinate, yellow to ochre-green flowers (
<emphasis id="C0B3EA86FFDAFFEA2CC68E72FA31F8A5" box="[1421,1451,1820,1845]" italics="true" pageId="4">vs.</emphasis>
resupinate, amber-yellow), the ovate dorsal sepal, 
<quantity id="353F9B71FFDAFFEA2B868E51FC8BF8C9" box="[717,785,1855,1882]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="4" unit="mm" value="5.0">5 mm</quantity>
long (
<emphasis id="C0B3EA86FFDAFFEA2A148E2EFCE4F8C9" box="[863,894,1856,1881]" italics="true" pageId="4">vs.</emphasis>
elliptic, 
<quantity id="353F9B71FFDAFFEA2AAD8E51FBEAF8C9" box="[998,1136,1855,1881]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5999999999999996" metricValueMax="3.8" metricValueMin="3.4" pageId="4" unit="mm" value="3.5999999999999996" valueMax="3.8" valueMin="3.4">3.4–3.8 mm</quantity>
long), the ovate petals (
<emphasis id="C0B3EA86FFDAFFEA2CC68E2EFA31F8C9" box="[1421,1451,1856,1881]" italics="true" pageId="4">vs.</emphasis>
oblong), and an entire lip with 5-keels and 2-lobed apex (
<emphasis id="C0B3EA86FFDAFFEA2A428E0AFCB2F8ED" box="[777,808,1892,1917]" italics="true" pageId="4">vs.</emphasis>
sub-3-lobed, with seven minute keels and truncate apex). 
<taxonomicName id="35C74D17FFDAFFEA29C38EE9FD8BF831" authority="Dodson (1980" authorityName="Dodson" authorityYear="1980" box="[136,529,1927,1953]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Epidendrum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="4" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="jativae">
<emphasis id="C0B3EA86FFDAFFEA29C38EE9FEFCF831" box="[136,358,1927,1953]" italics="true" pageId="4">Epidendrum jativae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="96564B65FFDAFFEA28268EE9FD8BF831" author="Dodson, C. H. &amp; Dodson, P. M." box="[365,529,1927,1953]" pageId="4" pagination="85" refId="ref13689" refString="Dodson, C. H. &amp; Dodson, P. M. (1980) Epidendrum jativae Dodson. In: Dodson, C. H. (Ed.) Orchids of Ecuador. Icones Plantarum Tropicarum 4: pl. 85." type="journal article" year="1980">Dodson (1980</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
: pl. 85) differs in the non-resupinate flowers, green suffused with burgundy red to purplish brown (
<emphasis id="C0B3EA86FFDAFFEA280B8EC2FEC5F855" box="[320,351,1964,1989]" italics="true" pageId="4">vs.</emphasis>
resupinate, amber-yellow), elliptic-obovate dorsal sepal (
<emphasis id="C0B3EA86FFDAFFEA2A958EC2FC66F855" box="[990,1020,1964,1989]" italics="true" pageId="4">vs.</emphasis>
elliptic), petals 
<quantity id="353F9B71FFDAFFEA2DE68EC5FB77F855" box="[1197,1261,1963,1989]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="4" unit="mm" value="6.0">6 mm</quantity>
long (
<emphasis id="C0B3EA86FFDAFFEA2C788EC2FAC8F855" box="[1331,1362,1964,1989]" italics="true" pageId="4">vs.</emphasis>
<quantity id="353F9B71FFDAFFEA2C1C8EC5FF2EF879" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.7" metricValueMax="3.9" metricValueMin="3.5" pageId="4" unit="mm" value="3.7" valueMax="3.9" valueMin="3.5">3.5–3.9 mm</quantity>
long), and an entire lip with 3 keels and 4-lobed apex (
<emphasis id="C0B3EA86FFDAFFEA2A788EBEFCC8F879" box="[819,850,2000,2025]" italics="true" pageId="4">vs.</emphasis>
sub-3-lobed, with 7 minute keels and truncate apex) (
<bibRefCitation id="96564B65FFDAFFEA29DB8E9DFE25F79E" author="Santiago, E. &amp; Hagsater, E." box="[144,447,2035,2062]" pageId="4" pagination="847" refId="ref15994" refString="Santiago, E. &amp; Hagsater, E. (2006) Epidendrum jativae Dodson. The genus Epidendrum, Part 5. Icones Orchidacearum 8: pl. 847. [Instituto Chinoin, Mexico]." type="journal article" year="2006">Santiago &amp; Hágsater 2006</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
